<br>
Reine was pacing in his room thinking of what he should do, what can be done with the demons that roam the grounds. At the moment they are able to stop their advance plunging the human world to nothingness. It was a terrible thing to happen, the last bastion humanity threatened by the evil that was unleashed. It was not only the human population that was in trouble, the other races were also in peril. <br>
<br>
With the number of monsters lurking the land, even their combined military cannot push the demons back. IT should be something else, soemthing to at least weaken the demons. <br>
<br>
Though the elves were able to hold the demons back without losing their territories. Whatever the reason is they were able to and he will have to find it out.<br>
<br>
He was able to gain permition to travel to the lands of the elves with everything that he needs. Stealth is the key so bringing the whole army is out of the question. He may ask for some few people but would not demand it from them. He has informed the soldiers under him that if they are willing to take the mission they are to meet in the gillbars bar. He was going to recruit more people in there.<br>
<br>
<br>
Gathering his thoughts, he went out of his room, through the corridors and out of the barracks. The people of the city are all braced to what might eventually be the end of all civilisation. Dread can be seen in their eyes, hope is almost lost. <br>
<br>
